	 The procedure is&nbsp;indicated&nbsp;if:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>no&nbsp;or&nbsp;too few spermatozoa in&nbsp;a&nbsp;male partner’s ejaculate or&nbsp;his sperm motility is&nbsp;low;</li>
	<li>ejaculation does not occur, there is&nbsp;an&nbsp;erectile or&nbsp;other sexual dysfunctions;</li>
	<li>spermatozoa cannot penetrate into the uterine cavity through the cervical mucus.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	 Intrauterine insemination is&nbsp;possible if&nbsp;at&nbsp;least one fallopian tube in&nbsp;a&nbsp;woman is&nbsp;not blocked.
</p>
